cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.CR

The paper discusses a framework for processing and analyzing large volumes of unstructured log data generated by HPC systems. This involves distributed NoSQL databases and the Apache Spark framework for in-memory processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with data management and analytics, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper discusses system behavior and root cause analysis, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
